            </p>
            <div class="col-1">
                <img class="image-center" src="assets/images/walkthroughs/1A-click-login-link.jpg" alt="Forgot Username or Password Step 1" style="height: auto; width: auto; max-width: 80%; cursor: pointer;" onclick="showImage('assets/images/walkthroughs/1A-click-login-link.jpg')">
            </div>
            <p class="item-center" style="font-size: 22px; padding-top: 40px;">
                2)&nbsp;&nbsp;NEXT, click on the blue link that says "Forgotten my username or password", just below the Login button.
                <br>See the red arrow and box in the following image (click to enlarge):
            </p>
            <div class="col-1">
                <img class="image-center" src="assets/images/walkthroughs/2A-forgot-username-password.png" alt="Forgot Username or Password Step 2" style="height: auto; width: auto; max-width: 80%; cursor: pointer;" onclick="showImage('assets/images/walkthroughs/2A-forgot-username-password.png')">
            </div>
            <p class="item-center" style="font-size: 22px;">
                3)&nbsp;&nbsp;FINALLY, enter the email address associated with your account, (usually your @mencapliverpool.org.uk email address). After entering the email address for your account, click the blue "Reset Password" button.
                <br>See the red arrows in the following image (click to enlarge):
            </p>
            <div class="col-1">
                <img class="image-center" src="assets/images/walkthroughs/2B-reset-account-by-email.png" alt="Forgot Username or Password Step 3" style="height: auto; width: auto; max-width: 80%; cursor: pointer;" onclick="showImage('assets/images/walkthroughs/2B-reset-account-by-email.png')">
            </div>
            <p class="item-center" style="font-size: 25px;">
                NOTE: An email will be sent to that email address inbox (check spam or junk folders too) within a minute or two, which has your username and a newly reset password. Use these to login through the usual way, and you can then chane your password through account management.
            </p>
        </div>

