            <h1 id="gallery-upload-help" class="item-center">Uploading a New Image to the Gallery</h1>
            <p class="item-center" style="font-size: 22px;">
                1)&nbsp;&nbsp;FIRST, from any page, click on the "Login" button, found in the bottom right corner of your screen, found on the footer. On the next page enter your login details.
                <br>See the red arrow and circle in the following image (click to enlarge):
            </p>
            <div class="col-1">
                <img class="image-center" src="assets/images/walkthroughs/1A-click-login-link.jpg" alt="Upload to the Gallery Step 1" style="height: auto; width: auto; max-width: 80%; cursor: pointer;" onclick="showImage('assets/images/walkthroughs/1A-click-login-link.jpg')">
            </div>
            <p class="item-center" style="font-size: 22px; padding-top: 40px;">
                2)&nbsp;&nbsp;NEXT, now that you are logged in, click the "Gallery" menu button, on the left side of your screen. This will take you to the Gallery page.
                <br>See the red arrows and red boxes in the following image (click to enlarge):
            </p>
            <div class="col-1">
                <img class="image-center" src="assets/images/walkthroughs/4A-gallery.png" alt="Upload to the Gallery Step 2" style="height: auto; width: auto; max-width: 80%; cursor: pointer;" onclick="showImage('assets/images/walkthroughs/4A-gallery.png')">
            </div>
            <p class="item-center" style="font-size: 22px;">
                3)&nbsp;&nbsp;NOW, to upload a new image first choose an image from your device, making sure your image is named correctly, as people will download the image with the same file name you upload it with. Think visually impaired users, so descriptive when naming photos/videos.
